                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.002 Mussolini/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-01T23:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 1, 1931—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—7:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. All the papers report fully the Butler incident and are unanimous in stating
                    that it has been correctly handled, that satisfaction is complete and that as
                    far as Italy is concerned the incident is closed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
